    "comment": "Rationale: Fig. 3: colocalization of ApoE with Synapsin I\nFig. 4: biochemical fractionation confirms synaptic localization of ApoE, colocalization of ApoE with vGlut1 and Map2\n\nNOTE: ApoE is a secreted proteins, therfore only synaptic cleft annotation is made. The colocalization with vGlut1 in synaptoneurosome showed in Fig.4 suggests that ApoE is localized at glutamatergic synapses.. Experimental description: Experiments with human brain tissue form buject with Alzheimer's disease or\nno cognitive deficits. These experiments are featured in Fig. 3 and Fig. 4\n\nLiteral M&M\n\"Subjects\nBrains from human subjects with a diagnosis of Alzheimer's disease or\nno cognitive deficits were obtained through the Massachusetts\nAlzheimer's Disease Research Centre and Massachusetts General\nHospital Neuropathology department.\"",
